definition.value: A hydroxypiperidine that is duvoglustat in which the amino hydrogen is replaced by a methyl group. It is an inhibitor of alpha-glucosidase, an agonist of the glucose sensor SGLT3 and exhibits anti-HIV activity.
Any glycosyloxyflavone that consists of a flavonol attached to a xylosylglycosyl residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage.
A glycerate that is the conjugate base of D-glyceric acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.
